<br>
Assumption 1) something must be done to downgrade the current level of effectiveness of the evade skill<br>
<br>
Assumption 2) if assumption 1 is met, there WILL be a reduction in the damage output of Rogues. After all, if we are not doing too much damage with the way evade currently works, why do we need to change evade?<br>
<br>
I do not have a problem with these assumptions. I have always had a bit of a problem with the straight up slug fest that we as rogues now find our selves in. Not very roguely at all (yes I place RP and character definition above raw combat effectiveness, otherwise I would not have been playing this class for well over a year). <br>
<br>
Suggestion) Reduce the effectiveness of Evade, but allow US to decide when and how much we will employ it. Reduce the evade cycle time a comparable amount and make it harder to interrupt. This allows us to choose when we will be building up hate, and when we will be lowering it. KEEP IN MIND, we have to turn off auto-attack to evade, thus more time attempting to evade=less time dealing damage.<br>
<br>
<br>
The real problem arises from the fact that in a few shorts seconds (assuming the evade is not interupted and does not fail) we can currently offset many more rounds of damage than it takes for the evade to cycle through and be ready for use again. Thus if we are lucky we can go through a whole fight at near maximum damage output with minimal damage to ourselves. With the suggested fix, we can only offset a few rounds of damage, WITH THE SAME LENGTHY CYCLE before evade is ready again. This will lead to frustration on the part of those who do the smart/selfish thing and go sit down for a while (assuming they can even withdraw from the fight in good order) and death to those who insist on staying in and contributing to the fight.<br>
<br>
 So reduce the effectiveness and increase the frequency with which we can attempt to evade. This forces us to decide wether we want to be dealing damage at a specific instance, or removing the hate we have accumulated. From a RP point of view this fits better with my own view of how a rogue should be fighting anyway. Looking for openings, darting in to take advantage of them, then darting back out again. Not standing toe to toe and slugging it out and then waving a magic wand that makes our opponent forget we are a threat.<br>
<br>
In summary, if you drastically reduce the efffectiveness of evade (as all of the official solutions WILL do) AND make it cycle much faster, you will have your goal : reduced overall damage IF the rogue decides lowering agro is more important than making maximum damage potential. <br>
<br>
I just hate the idea of sitting on my butt waiting to move down the hate list while my friends are dying. Let me do SOMETHING. Anything. But most importantly, let ME decide when to do it.<br>
<br>
Kristar Shadowdancer<br>
39th Level Rogue<br>
The Twilight Fellowship<br>
